### ============================================================
### Vendor Invoice Management - Service Test Suite
### Requires the "REST Client" extension in VS Code / BAS
### Run: cds watch   (keep it running in a separate terminal)
### Click "Send Request" above any block below to run it.
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:42565

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 1. ADMIN SERVICE
### ------------------------------------------------------------

### 1.1 Get all vendors (Admin sees everything)
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Vendors
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123

### 1.2 Get all invoices (should return 20)
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123

### 1.3 Create a new DRAFT invoice for an APPROVED vendor (Acme Corp)
# Expected: 201 Created, status = DRAFT
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoiceNumber": "INV-TEST-001",
  "vendor_ID": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111101",
  "invoiceDate": "2026-06-01",
  "dueDate": "2026-07-01",
  "amount": 10000.00,
  "currency": "USD"
}

### 1.4 Try creating an invoice for a PENDING vendor (New Vendor Inc)
# Expected: 400 error "Please select an approved vendor"
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoiceNumber": "INV-TEST-002",
  "vendor_ID": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111104",
  "invoiceDate": "2026-06-01",
  "dueDate": "2026-07-01",
  "amount": 5000.00,
  "currency": "USD"
}

### 1.5 Try a future-dated invoice
# Expected: 400 error "Invoice date cannot be in the future"
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoiceNumber": "INV-TEST-003",
  "vendor_ID": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111101",
  "invoiceDate": "2027-01-01",
  "dueDate": "2027-02-01",
  "amount": 5000.00,
  "currency": "USD"
}

### 1.6 Try a negative / out-of-range amount
# Expected: 400 error "Amount must be between 0.01 and 1,000,000"
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoiceNumber": "INV-TEST-004",
  "vendor_ID": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111101",
  "invoiceDate": "2026-06-01",
  "dueDate": "2026-07-01",
  "amount": -100,
  "currency": "USD"
}

### 1.7 Get the invoice you created in 1.3 (copy its ID from the 1.3 response)
# Replace {{invoiceId}} below manually after running 1.3
@invoiceId = d7a2f1a7-0005-4812-ab7f-457ca636a22a

GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices({{invoiceId}})
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123

### 1.8 Add a line item to that invoice
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/InvoiceItems
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoice_ID": "{{invoiceId}}",
  "lineNumber": 1,
  "description": "Consulting Services",
  "quantity": 2,
  "unitPrice": 5000.00
}

### 1.9 Try to submit BEFORE adding any line items
# Expected: 400 "Invoice must have at least one line item" (only fails if run before 1.8)
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices({{invoiceId}})/AdminService.submitForApproval
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 1.10 Submit for approval (after line item from 1.8 exists, sum = amount)
# Expected: status changes to SUBMITTED
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices({{invoiceId}})/AdminService.submitForApproval
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 1.11 Invoice analytics (grouped by vendor/status/currency)
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/InvoiceAnalytics
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123


### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 2. APPROVER SERVICE
### ------------------------------------------------------------

### 2.1 Admin cannot approve their own submitted invoice
# Expected: 400 "You cannot approve your own submitted invoice"
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/approver/Invoices({{invoiceId}})/ApproverService.approveInvoice
Authorization: Basic admin@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{ "comments": "Trying to approve my own invoice" }

### 2.2 Approver approves the invoice (different user than submitter)
# Expected: status -> APPROVED
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/approver/Invoices({{invoiceId}})/ApproverService.approveInvoice
Authorization: Basic approver1@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{ "comments": "Invoice approved after document verification" }

### 2.3 Try rejecting an already-approved invoice
# Expected: 400 "Only submitted invoices can be rejected"
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/approver/Invoices({{invoiceId}})/ApproverService.rejectInvoice
Authorization: Basic approver1@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{ "reason": "Too late, already approved" }

### 2.4 Reject a real SUBMITTED invoice (use INV-002, already SUBMITTED in sample data)
@submittedInvoiceId = 22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222220002

### 2.4a Try to reject WITHOUT a reason
# Expected: 400 "Rejection reason is mandatory"
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/approver/Invoices({{submittedInvoiceId}})/ApproverService.rejectInvoice
Authorization: Basic approver1@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 2.4b Reject WITH a reason
# Expected: status -> REJECTED
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/approver/Invoices({{submittedInvoiceId}})/ApproverService.rejectInvoice
Authorization: Basic approver1@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{ "reason": "Missing supporting documents" }

### 2.5 View all submitted/approved invoices (Approver has read access to all)
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/approver/Invoices
Authorization: Basic approver1@company.com:pass123


### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 3. VENDOR SERVICE (row-level security)
### ------------------------------------------------------------

### 3.1 manager1 sees ONLY their assigned vendors (Acme Corp, Global Supplies, Quality Parts)
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/vendor/Vendors
Authorization: Basic manager1@company.com:pass123

### 3.2 manager1 sees ONLY invoices for their assigned vendors
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/vendor/Invoices
Authorization: Basic manager1@company.com:pass123

### 3.3 manager2 should see a DIFFERENT set of vendors/invoices
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/vendor/Invoices
Authorization: Basic manager2@company.com:pass123

### 3.4 manager1 creates an invoice for THEIR OWN vendor (Acme Corp) - should succeed
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/vendor/Invoices
Authorization: Basic manager1@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoiceNumber": "INV-TEST-M1-001",
  "vendor_ID": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111101",
  "invoiceDate": "2026-06-01",
  "dueDate": "2026-07-01",
  "amount": 3000.00,
  "currency": "USD"
}

### 3.5 manager1 tries to create an invoice for a vendor NOT assigned to them (Tech Solutions)
# Expected: 403/400 "You can only create invoices for your assigned vendors"
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/vendor/Invoices
Authorization: Basic manager1@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoiceNumber": "INV-TEST-M1-002",
  "vendor_ID": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111102",
  "invoiceDate": "2026-06-01",
  "dueDate": "2026-07-01",
  "amount": 3000.00,
  "currency": "USD"
}

### 3.6 manager1 tries to read an invoice belonging to manager2's vendor (e.g. INV-002, Tech Solutions)
# Expected: empty result / not found (row-level security blocks it)
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/vendor/Invoices(22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222220002)
Authorization: Basic manager1@company.com:pass123


### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 4. VIEWER SERVICE (read-only, approved invoices only)
### ------------------------------------------------------------

### 4.1 Viewer sees only APPROVED (or PAID) invoices
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/viewer/Invoices
Authorization: Basic viewer1@company.com:pass123

### 4.2 Viewer sees only APPROVED vendors
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/viewer/Vendors
Authorization: Basic viewer1@company.com:pass123

### 4.3 Viewer tries to POST (create) an invoice - should fail, service is read-only
# Expected: 405 Method Not Allowed or 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/viewer/Invoices
Authorization: Basic viewer1@company.com:pass123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoiceNumber": "INV-SHOULD-FAIL",
  "vendor_ID": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111101",
  "invoiceDate": "2026-06-01",
  "amount": 1000.00,
  "currency": "USD"
}


### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 5. NEGATIVE / UNAUTHORIZED ACCESS
### ------------------------------------------------------------

### 5.1 No credentials at all - should be blocked (401/403), not an empty array
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices

### 5.2 Viewer tries to access Admin-only service
# Expected: 403 Forbidden
GET {{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/admin/Invoices
Authorization: Basic viewer1@company.com:pass123
